messages.message:
Patch Set 8:

This patch is not enough to produce tools that would be working together with the modern kernel this is aimed at.
This is all thanks to test tools that use O_LOV_DELAY_CREATE directly without any compats or fallbacks.

Right now as a stop gp measure I am forced to add a patch like this which we probably should make to be part of this patch?
(since tet tools probably go hand in hand with clients, we should not worry too much about compat I would think?)

diff --git a/lustre/tests/mpi/cascading_rw.c b/lustre/tests/mpi/cascading_rw.c
index 1d73fad..39e8a2a 100644
--- a/lustre/tests/mpi/cascading_rw.c
+++ b/lustre/tests/mpi/cascading_rw.c
@@ -82,7 +82,7 @@ void rw_file(char *name, long stride, unsigned int seed)
                 lum.lmm_stripe_count = 0;
                 lum.lmm_stripe_offset = -1;

-                fd = open(filename, O_CREAT | O_RDWR | O_LOV_DELAY_CREATE,
+                fd = open(filename, O_CREAT | O_RDWR | O_LOV_DELAY_CREATE_MASK,
                           FILEMODE);
                 if (fd == -1) {
                         sprintf(errmsg, "open of file %s", filename);
